description Test underlining in diagnostic output.
program diagnostic-output
file file1 <>
This is line one without tabs.
	This line has a tab at the beginning.
This line has	a tab in the middle.
end-of-inline-data
stdin
read file1
note {file1 1 1 0} start of line, zero width
note {file1 1 1 1} start of line, width 1
note {file1 2 1 1} just the tab
note {file1 2 2 1} past the tab
note {file1 1 18 7} no tabs in line
note {file1 2 29 9} tab at beginning
note {file1 3 28 6} tab in middle
end-of-inline-data
stderr
file1:1:1: note: start of line, zero width
This is line one without tabs.
^
file1:1:1: note: start of line, width 1
This is line one without tabs.
^
file1:2:1: note: just the tab
        This line has a tab at the beginning.
^^^^^^^^
file1:2:2: note: past the tab
        This line has a tab at the beginning.
        ^
file1:1:18: note: no tabs in line
This is line one without tabs.
                 ^^^^^^^
file1:2:29: note: tab at beginning
        This line has a tab at the beginning.
                                   ^^^^^^^^^
file1:3:28: note: tab in middle
This line has   a tab in the middle.
                             ^^^^^^
end-of-inline-data
